SUMMARIZER="I">

Although he is ranked as the richest man in the nation, Sam Walton is just another 
neighbor to folks in Bentonville, Arkansas.  The founder to the third-largest retail chain 
prefers bird hunting, tennis, and opening new stores to talking about his money.  For the 
third year in a row, Forbes magazine named him among the top billionaires in the world, 
with an estimated $8.7 billion.  Forbes first listed Walton as the richest man in the nation 
in 1985, drawing worldwide attention to Bentonville.  Walton has declined to comment.  
He reportedly spends four days a week visiting stores and talking to employees.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d066"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP900507-0207"
